be.docarch.odt2braille
Class HandlePEF

java.lang.Object
  be.docarch.odt2braille.HandlePEF

public class HandlePEF
extends java.lang.Object

This class handles the processing of a .pef file. The .pef file can be converted to a generic braille file convertToFile or an embosser-specific braille file embossToFile. In addition, the .pef file can be printed on a braille embosser (embossToDevice).

Author:
Bert Frees

embossToDevice

public boolean embossToDevice(java.lang.String deviceName)
                       throws java.io.IOException,
                              javax.print.PrintException,
                              javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException,
                              org.xml.sax.SAXException,
                              UnsupportedWidthException,
                              EmbosserFactoryException
Print the .pef file on a braille embosser. The embosser type is specified in the braille settings. If the "Interpoint 55" was selected, the .pef file is converted to a .brf file that can be interpreted by the wprint55 program, and wprint55 is executed. Otherwise, the .pef file is converted to the appropriate embosser-specific braille format with embossToFile and send to the specified printer device.

Parameters:
deviceName - The name of the printer device.
Throws:
java.io.IOException
javax.print.PrintException
javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException
org.xml.sax.SAXException
UnsupportedWidthException
EmbosserFactoryException
